  ## Set up a project using Next.js
  
  First, create a folder named _‘_ **_nextjs-firebase_** _’_ on your computer to store the web app project you want to build. Then, open Visual Studio Code (VS Code) and open that folder inside VS Code.
  
  Next, open the terminal in VS Code by clicking _Terminal → New Terminal_ (or press **Ctrl + \`** on your keyboard) to install the Next.js framework.
  
  Press enter or click to view image in full size
  
  ![](https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/1*n484sDAeEbaKeEa5hJOgXg.png)
  
  We will install Next.js version 16 (the latest version for now) using the instructions provided directly by the official [Next.js website](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/getting-started/installation).
  
  - In the VS Code terminal, make sure the last path shown is the name of your project folder ( _nextjs-firebase_).
  
  Press enter or click to view image in full size
  
  ![](https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/1*syZbDlnYXv6XcLJdrrWoCA.png)
  
  - Install Next.js using the following command:
  
  ```
  npx create-next-app@latest .
  ```
  
  > **Note:** The dot (`.`) means you are installing Next.js in the current/active folder (which is **_nextjs-firebase_**).
  
  - Then, select _‘_ **_Yes, use recommended defaults’,_** and press Enter.
  
  Press enter or click to view image in full size
  
