  ## Creating UI Components in Next.js
  
  As explained earlier, the main folder of our application is located inside the `app/` folder. This is where we will create the components for the login page of the application we are building.
  
  To create UI components in Next.js, we typically use a library called [**shadcn/ui**](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs). This library is very popular and has become a standard choice among Next.js developers when building UI components for their web applications.
  
  We will set up and install shadcn/ui based on the official documentation from its website ( [https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/installation/next](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/installation/next)).
  
  - First, install shadcn/ui through the VS Code terminal by typing the following command:
  
  ```
  npx shadcn@latest init
  ```
  
  > Note: To install shadcn/ui, it is highly recommended to stop the running Next.js project first. To stop it, you can press **Ctrl + C** on your keyboard, and the web app will stop running.
  
  Press enter or click to view image in full size
  
